data.description: Introducing 416 Mac Donough Street, an early twentieth century historic barrel-front limestone located on a gorgeous tree-lined block in Bedford Stuyvesant, nestled between Stuyvesant Avenue & Malcolm X Boulevard. This 3,120 sq ft townhouse is being utilized as a single family, but it can be reconfigured to your specifications as there is no certificate of occupancy. The current layout of the property includes a formal dining and living area on the garden level, with a separate windowed kitchen, laundry nook, full bath, along with access to the lush backyard as well as the unfinished basement. On the parlor and top level, you will find six bedrooms, all of which have bright exposures, three additional rooms, and two full baths. 416 Mac Donough is located on a designated landmarked street, will be delivered vacant, needs attention, has plenty of original details, and hardwood parquet flooring throughout. Building dimensions: 20 ft x 50 ft, lot size: 20 ft x 100 ft, and 880 sq feet of additional FAR. The Bedford Historic District contains some of Brooklyns most distinctive and well-preserved late-19th to 20th-century streetscapes. This property is only a short jaunt from the A/C trains at Utica Av or the J/Z trains at Gates Av, as well as local favorites such as Peaches, Trad Room, LunÃ€tico, Saraghina Pizzeria, Grandchamps Kitchen & Market and the YMCA. Note, the listing photos have been virtually decluttered.
